<TITLE> Mirza Azizul announces budget on June 7 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 30 (bdnews24.com) - The interim government is to announce the national budget for fiscal 2007-08 on June 7, finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam said Wednesday. The supplementary budget for the fiscal 2006-2007 and the budget for 2007-2008 would be placed simultaneously. Islam disclosed the budget announcement date after addressing the inaugural session of a seminar "Dissemination of research results," organised by the Social Science Research Council of the Planning Ministry, as chief guest. The budget would be the first full-fledged one prepared and placed by a caretaker government. Earlier in 1996, Prof Wahiduddin Mahmud, then finance adviser placed a temporary budget. The finance adviser, however, did not say anything about the venue for the budget announcement. He, however, did say that it would be telecasted live on Bangladesh Television. Chief adviser, advisers, government high officials, dignitaries, diplomats and journalists are to witness the announcement and be given copies of the budget papers. Finance ministry officials have said that the government has taken steps in the upcoming budget to enhance efficiency and effectiveness in public expenditure and ensure achieving goals of the poverty reduction strategy. The budget would also focus on boosting revenue income. "The government will explore alternative ways to increase the non-NBR revenue as well as non-tax revenue to boost its overall incomes amidst poor growth of earnings by the National Board of Revenue (NBR)," a senior finance ministry official told bdnews24.com. bd
